name: Kulidan Kitchen & Space
address: Banjar Wangbung, Jalan Garuda Wisnu, Guwang, Kec. Sukawati, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80582, Indonesia
review 1:
Great place with an awesome indoor/outdoor vibe, and a lovely team‚ò∫Ô∏è
It‚Äôs a big space surrounded by rice fields and plenty of gorgeous plants, and the air flow is amazing so we spent a few hours working and brunching.
The menu has a great lot of options to choose from, and the mee goreng is derish!! ü§§
The onion rings is a specialty and a must try!!
We also had the chicken burger and finished with the French toast, both equally tasty.

review 2: Love this hidden gem tucked away in the rice fields. The food is amazing, super fairly priced, and everyone who works there is so sweet. name: kulidancoffee

review 1: this place is perfect for working, hanging out, and very comfortable. the food and drinks are delicious and pocket-friendly, the view is also beautiful and you can enjoy the rice fields. Hurry up and stop by for a recommendation
review 2: Great Place! Delicious coffee, I found this through Google and would recommend anyone to visit.  Simple menu for food with bonus of nice thick cookies and pastries.  Nice initiative with a gallery of art made from plastic waste collected on the beach.  Friendly staff, lovely garden and views, good music at the right volume.  Great ambience and venue for a hidden coffee spot!  I will be back =)

name: Guwang Barong & Keris Dance
address: Guwang, Sukawati, Gianyar Regency, Bali 80582, Indonesia
review 1:
I take my guest 4 person adult
Very good performance with strong frekuensi of theta wave.
review 2: Guwang Barong & Keris Dance is a stunning Balinese dance show that tells the story of the epic battle between the Barong, the good spirit, and Rangda, the evil witch. The show features amazing costumes, masks, music, and drama that will immerse you in the local culture and folklore. The show is held every day at 9:30 am at a comfortable venue in Guwang. You can buy the tickets at the venue for a cheap price. You can also check out their IG account for more information and videos. This show is a must-see for anyone who visits Bali. It is a captivating and educational experience that you will never forget.

name: Tri Datu Palace
address: Guwang, Sukawati, Gianyar Regency, Bali 80582, Indonesia
review 1:
Our stay in Tri Datu Palace was very good. Authentic house and friendly staff made our stay comfortable and easy. Everything was clean there. I liked that the pool is half covered with a roof, so there is also a shadow in the part of the pool - for me it is important as I do not like staying long under the sun in the middle of the day. The Owner Chok and his wife were very friendly and helped us in various issues to make our stay pleasant. If anything broke or we needed any items they immediately brought it to us.
The location is also good as you are about 30 min away from Ubud and Sanur by bike.
review 2:
I was visiting the sensational Kulidan kitchen and space and wanted to stay somewhere nearby for a couple of nights. Tri Datu Palace was recommended to me and I couldn‚Äôt have asked for something better. The villa I stayed in was one of two stilted timber dwellings, suspended above a swimming pool. The villas have extensive farmland views.

The village centre‚Äôs warungs, which line the main road, serve local fare at local prices. If you want a peaceful break and genuine Balinese experience, I recommend Tri Datu Palace.
